msContents.summary: Two collections of drawings of bridles, curbs, bits, and harnesses, one with simpler drawings and notes in Italian added by a later hand to most of the drawings (Volume 1, f. 1r-37v), and a second with more elaborate drawings of bridles, curbs, bits, and harnesses, without text (Volume 2).

support.watermark: Volume 1: WM in ornate square frame, 3 crescents of descending size in a horizontal row (similar to Crescents, nos. 138-139, in David Woodward, Catalogue of watermarks in Italian printed maps ca. 1540-1600) and a countermark of HB or IB surmounted by a trefoil (similar to Woodward, Letters, nos. 299-301); Volume 2: similar to Briquet Armoires 2231-2239, arms of the town of Schrobenhausen (Prague or Austria, mid- and late-16th century).

supportDesc.extent: 2 volumes (46, 31 leaves) : Volume 1: 436 x 295 mm. bound to 445 x 305 mm.; Volume 2: 434 x 285 mm. bound to 435 x 290 mm

collation.p: Volume 1: Paper, i + 46 + i; 1¹⁸ 2²⁸; [1-46], modern foliation in pencil, lower right recto. Volume 2: Paper, i + 31; 1-10² 11⁶ 12⁶(-1, pastedown); [1-31] (21-31 blank), modern foliation in pencil, lower right recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Later notes written in cursive script (Volume 1).

binding.p: Volume 1: parchment over pasteboards with remnants of 2 pairs of green fabric ties, inscription No. 34 in ink on upper cover; Volume 2: half pigskin, blind-rolled and -stamped, over green parchment cut with double-fillet border, with remnants of 4 pairs of green fabric ties.

origin.p: Volume 1: drawn in Germany or Italy in the second half of the 16th century with notes added later in Italy; Volume 2: drawn in Prague or Austria (based on watermark) in the second half of the 16th century.
origin.origPlace: Germany or Italy and Prague or Austria

history.provenance: Sold by Antiquariat Konrad Meuschel (Bad Honnef am Rhein, Germany) to Lawrence J. Schoenberg, Feb. 1999.
Deposit by Lawrence J. Schoenberg and Barbara Brizdle, 2012.
